<p>I have up to four parameters to accept on my site so I've added the following to my .htaccess.</p>  <pre><code>RewriteEngine On RewriteRule ^([^/]*)/([^/]*)/([^/]*)/([^/]*)$ /index.php?atr=$1&amp;dir=$2&amp;query=$3&amp;lookup=$4 [L] RewriteRule ^([^/]*)/([^/]*)/([^/]*)$ /index.php?atr=$1&amp;dir=$2&amp;query=$3 [L] RewriteRule ^([^/]*)/([^/]*)$ /index.php?atr=$1&amp;dir=$2 [L]  RewriteRule ^([^/]*)$ /index.php?atr=$1 [L] </code></pre>  <p>All was working fine until I added the fifth line to allow only one parameter. This returns 500 errors in all instances of index.php with the error:</p>  <pre><code>Request exceeded the limit of 10 internal redirects </code></pre>